  "fun_fact": "Microplastics are now found literally everywhere — from the deepest point on Earth (the Mariana Trench) to clouds, and even inside the human body. The average person is estimated to consume about 5 grams of microplastics every week — roughly the weight of a credit card. Cutting single-use plastics and switching to alternatives like steel, glass, and cloth is one of the most direct ways to reduce plastic at the source.",
